# basic commands
- whoami : user you are
- pwd : current directory
- ls : files in current directory
- cat : shows the content of a file
- sudo -i : switch to root user 
- cd / : go to the directory 
- cd .. : go back to previus directory
- cd /bin : commands available for the user, user files executable
- cd /sbin : root user executable commands
- cd /etc : configuration files, example -- hostname file
- cd /temp : temp files of system and programs 
- cd /bot : kernel files, booting parameters
- exit : back to user (root logout)
- mkdir : create a dir 
- touch file.txt : create a file in the current directory empty
- cp file1.txt dev/ : copy file from source to destination
- cp -r dir1 dir2/ : copy one directory to another
- command --help : shows how to use the command
- mv file1.txt dir1/  : move a file to a directory
- mv file1.txt file1_newname.txt : rename a file 
- mv *.txt dir1/ : move all  txt files to the directory
- rm file.txt : remove the file 
- rm -r dir1/ : remove the directory



